name: mono-methyl_phthalate
source: Aldrich Chemical Company; Aldrich Catalog-Handbook of Fine Chemicals; Milwaukee; WI; 1984.
Reason: 1,1-propanediol, 3-(2-methoxyphenoxy)-, 1-carbam has a melting point of 92 degrees Celsius. The basic unit of analysis is the 1,2-propanediol moiety, which on its own exhibits intermolecular hydrogen bonding, thus increasing the melting point. The methoxyphenoxy group introduces additional rigidity and molecular weight, which raises the melting point. The methoxy group also introduces additional hydrogen bonding potential, which can further lower the melting point. The carbamate group increases the melting point due to its ability to form intermolecular hydrogen bonds and increase molecular weight. The ether linkage reduces the melting point due to the reduced molecular weight and the absence of hydrogen bonding potential.
